# Trivy gate allowlist (S3, modernization-plan-v8 §6d) — read by the trivy-action
# "gate on actionable CVEs" step in .github/workflows/ci.yml.
#
# Each entry WAIVES a HIGH/CRITICAL container CVE that has a fix but cannot be
# remediated from warden/requirements.txt, with a justification and a review note.
# This is auditable (one reviewable line per CVE in git history), never a blanket
# `continue-on-error`. Prefer a requirements pin over an entry here whenever the
# package is a top-level dependency.

# CVE-2026-23949 — jaraco.context path traversal (HIGH).
# The flagged copy is VENDORED inside setuptools (`setuptools/_vendor/jaraco.context
# -5.3.0`), not a top-level import, so a requirements pin cannot replace it — only a
# setuptools release that vendors jaraco.context>=6.1.0 can. The vuln is a build-time
# path traversal that triggers only when *building* a malicious package; the runtime
# uvicorn image never builds packages from untrusted input, so it is not reachable in
# production. Revisit when bumping setuptools past a release that vendors the fix.
CVE-2026-23949
